text: Jacques-Abraham Durand d'Aubigny (1707 – 1776) was French diplomat and lawyer of the Ancien Régime. He was born on September 4, 1707 in Beaune. He was appointed a Chevalier de l'Ordre de St Lazare. ==See also== *List of Ambassadors of France to the United Kingdom ==References== Category:1707 births Category:1776 deaths Category:Ambassadors of France to the United Kingdom
